{"id": 6618, "title": "Ticket #6618: Consolidate timestamp functions", "description": "<blockquote>\nWe have multiple pieces of code that generate a unix epoch timestamp with sub-second resolution, which hide the differences in computing this across different platforms. They are roughly equivalent, but some have extra dead code and others compute less-precise values. They should be consolidated into one place.\n\n<p>The prime candidates for consolidation are the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=UtcTime\" title=\"Utc Time\">UtcTime</a></span> class and _condor_dprintf_gettime().</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Apr-03 13:11</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=54654\">[54654]</a></span>: Fix initialization of struct timeval variables. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6618\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6618'); return false;\" title=\"Consolidate timestamp functions\">#6618</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Apr-03 10:38</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=54653\">[54653]</a></span>: Replace <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=UtcTime\" title=\"Utc Time\">UtcTime</a></span> class with struct timeval and function to subtract them. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6618\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6618'); return false;\" title=\"Consolidate timestamp functions\">#6618</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Mar-30 14:14</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=54627\">[54627]</a></span>: Fix type mismatch in dprintf() format string. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6618\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6618'); return false;\" title=\"Consolidate timestamp functions\">#6618</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Mar-26 10:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=54619\">[54619]</a></span>: Convert more trival uses of <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=UtcTime\" title=\"Utc Time\">UtcTime</a></span> to condor_gettimestamp_double(). <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6618\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6618'); return false;\" title=\"Consolidate timestamp functions\">#6618</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Mar-23 15:42</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=54618\">[54618]</a></span>: Convert trivial uses of <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=UtcTime\" title=\"Utc Time\">UtcTime</a></span> to condor_gettimestamp_double(). <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6618\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6618'); return false;\" title=\"Consolidate timestamp functions\">#6618</a></span> Or to time() when the caller ignores the sub-second portion.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Mar-23 15:27</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=54617\">[54617]</a></span>: Consolidate functions to get timestamps with sub-second resolution. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6618\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6618'); return false;\" title=\"Consolidate timestamp functions\">#6618</a></span> <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=UtcTime\" title=\"Utc Time\">UtcTime</a></span> only provided millisecond resolution on windows and had two copies of the same time query code. _condor_dprintf_gettime() had better resolution, but was only available to the dprintf code.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2018-Mar-23 14:37</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=54616\">[54616]</a></span>: Use clock_gettime on MacOSX when available. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=6618\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('6618'); return false;\" title=\"Consolidate timestamp functions\">#6618</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2018-May-02 11:16", "status": "resolved", "created": "2018-Mar-21 15:30", "fixed_version": "2018-Mar-21 15:30", "broken_version": "", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "Libs", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "#6617", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}